# Example: 
@correlation_id = {{CORRELATION}}-3005

PATCH http://{{DFAPI_URL}}/{{FORM_TYPE}}/{{application_id}}/application/{{correlation_id}}
Authorization: Basic {{DFAPI_CREDENTIALS}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "applicationInfo": {
    "faxNo": "9999999999",
    "phoneNo": "8888888888"
  }
}



### QUERY PROHIBITION STATUS
############################
# Disconnect from VPN to run this command, or run on OpenShift pod.
# Example: http://digitalforms-api.c220ad-dev.svc/digitalforms/21900104/status/saf-ADP-182-21900104-3006

@correlation_id = {{CORRELATION}}-3006
GET http://{{DFAPI_URL}}/{{NOTICE_NUMBER}}/status/{{correlation_id}}
Authorization: Basic {{DFAPI_CREDENTIALS}}
Content-Type: application/json



### GET DISCLOSURE
##################
# Disconnect from VPN to run this command, or run on OpenShift pod.
# Example: GET http://digitalforms-api.c220ad-dev.svc/digitalforms/20/disclosure/saf-ADP-182-21900104-3007

@correlation_id = {{CORRELATION}}-3007
GET http://{{DFAPI_URL}}/{{DOCUMENT_ID}}/disclosure/{{correlation_id}}
Authorization: Basic {{DFAPI_CREDENTIALS}}
Content-Type: application/json



### MARK DISCLOSURE DOCUMENT AS SENT
####################################
# Disconnect from VPN to run this command, or run on OpenShift pod.
# Example: PATCH http://digitalforms-api.c220ad-dev.svc/digitalforms/disclosure/saf-ADP-182-21900104-3008

@correlation_id = {{CORRELATION}}-3008
PATCH http://{{DFAPI_URL}}/disclosure/{{correlation_id}}
Authorization: Basic {{DFAPI_CREDENTIALS}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "disclosure": {
    "disclosedDtm": "{{$datetime "YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm:ss -00:00"}}",
    "documentId": "{{DOCUMENT_ID}}"
  }
}


# >>> DISCLOSURE CHECK <<<
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Check that disclosure has happened by looking at the response from the QUERY endpoint.
# When a disclosure has not been sent, you should see the "disclosure" element prohibition query
# responses with no date. For example: 
#   "disclosure":[{"documentId":"1600"}]
# After the disclosure, the date is added, like this:
#   "disclosure":[{"documentId":"1600","disclosedDtm":"2021-12-20 09:41:25 -08:00"}]
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


### GET PAYMENT STATUS
######################
# Disconnect from VPN to run this command, or run on OpenShift pod.
# Example: http://digitalforms-api.c220ad-dev.svc/digitalforms/c741582c-de28-67e2-e054-00144ffbc109/payment/status/saf-ADP-182-21900104-3009
# NOTE: an HTTP 404 response with "Requested data not found" means that no payment has been made.

@correlation_id = {{CORRELATION}}-3009

GET http://{{DFAPI_URL}}/{{application_id}}/payment/status/{{correlation_id}}
Authorization: Basic {{DFAPI_CREDENTIALS}}
Content-Type: application/json


### PATCH PAYMENT
################
# Disconnect from VPN to run this command, or run on OpenShift pod.
# Example: http://digitalforms-api.c220ad-dev.svc/digitalforms/c741582c-de28-67e2-e054-00144ffbc109/payment/saf-ADP-182-21900104-3010
# NOTE: receipt number must be unique
@correlation_id = {{CORRELATION}}-3010
PATCH http://{{DFAPI_URL}}/{{application_id}}/payment/{{correlation_id}}
Authorization: Basic {{DFAPI_CREDENTIALS}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "transactionInfo":
  {
    "paymentAmount":"200.00",
    "paymentCardType":"VISA",
    "paymentDate":"{{$datetime "YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm:ss -00:00"}}",
    "receiptNumberTxt":"{{$randomInt 90000000 99999999}}"
  }
}

# >>> PAYMENT CHECK <<<
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Check that payment has happened by looking at the response from the GET PAYMENT STATUS endpoint.
# You should also see the receipt number from the QUERY STATUS endpoint.
#
# **NOTE**: The payment receipt number must be unique. That's why it's generated with a random int
# in the PATCH PAYMENT request above. If it's not unique, the payment will fail.
#
# When a payment has not been sent, you should see an empty "transactionInfo" element in the GET PAYMENT
# response. For example: 
#   "transactionInfo": {}
# After payment, the date is added, like this:
#    "transactionInfo":{"paymentCardType":"VISA","paymentAmount":"200.00","receiptNumberTxt":"90320189","paymentDate":"2022-01-07 15:13:48 -08:00"}
# The status endpoint shows the receipt number likes this:
#    "reviews":[{"applicationId":"d5066135-bf27-4c55-e054-00144ffb2e6c","receiptNumberTxt":"96237001"}]
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


### GET REVIEW SCHEDULE
#######################
# Disconnect from VPN to run this command, or run on OpenShift pod.
# Example: http://digitalforms-api.c220ad-dev.svc/digitalforms/ADP/ORAL/2021-07-16/review/availableTimeSlot/saf-ADP-182-21900104-3011
# Note: there should be no reviews on the weekends. Days with no reviews available return an HTTP 404.
@correlation_id = {{CORRELATION}}-3011

GET http://{{DFAPI_URL}}/{{FORM_TYPE}}/{{PRESENTATION_TYPE}}/{{$datetime "YYYY-MM-DD" 4 d}}/review/availableTimeSlot/{{correlation_id}}
Authorization: Basic {{DFAPI_CREDENTIALS}}
Content-Type: application/json



### SCHEDULE A REVIEW
#####################
# Disconnect from VPN to run this command, or run on OpenShift pod.
# Example: http://digitalforms-api.c220ad-dev.svc/digitalforms/c741582c-de28-67e2-e054-00144ffbc109/review/schedule/saf-ADP-182-21900104-3012
@correlation_id = {{CORRELATION}}-3012

POST http://{{DFAPI_URL}}/{{application_id}}/review/schedule/{{correlation_id}}
Authorization: Basic {{DFAPI_CREDENTIALS}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "timeSlot":
  {
    "reviewStartDtm":"2022-10-24 09:00:00 -07:00",
    "reviewEndDtm":"2022-10-24 09:30:00 -07:00"
  }
}

# >>> REVIEW CHECK <<<
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Check that review is booked by looking at the response from the QUERY endpoint.
# When no review is scheduled, you should see the "reviews" element prohibition query
# responses with no dates. For example: 
#   "reviews": [{"applicationId":"d5066135-bf23-4c55-e054-00144ffb2e6c"}]
# After payment, the "reviewStartDtm" and "reviewEndDtm" elements are added, like this:
#    "reviews": [{"applicationId":"d5066135-bf23-4c55-e054-00144ffb2e6c","status":"in_progress","reviewStartDtm":"2022-01-11 09:30:00 -08:00","reviewEndDtm":"2022-01-11 10:00:00 -08:00","receiptNumberTxt":"90320189","reviewId":"4010"}
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


### Now what?
#
# - Use the VIPS web front-end to mark the application as complete. Mark the review as unsuccessful. Check status.
# - Attempt to submit a new application for the same prohibition. 
#
#   **NOTE**: A second application should not work for ADP or IRP, but a UL prohibition is allowed to have a second review request. However, as of VIPS API 1.1.0, the VIPS API does allow ADP and UL prohibitions to be submitted again. After a discussion with Jonathan Longe in fall of 2021, we decided that it will not be possible for an applicant to submit a second application anyway, because the Digital Forms application system will check to see if an application already exists for each prohibition, and it will not attempt to create a second prohibition through the DFAPI anyway. So even though this is probably a defect in the DFAPI, it should never cause a problem.